 his late-Hellenistic followers. The further development of Aristotelian views in the late Hellenistic context is a long-neglected field of research.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEthics, Ancient. 0aPeripatetics. 4aAntike Philosophie. 4aEthik. 4aGlück. 4aGüterlehre. 4aRationalität. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAncient Philosophy.  aethics.  ahappiness.  arationality.  atheory of the good.1 aSzaif, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE UND GESCHICHTE 2010z9783110233612oZDB-23-DGE0 cprintz978311019307740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311021691240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110216912423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110216912/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGEb2010  aZDB-23-DGGb2010  aZDB-23-GPHc2000d2014